BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-RcppArmadillo 
Requires:         R-CRAN-Rcpp >= 0.12.6

%description
Collection of functions to evaluate sequences, decode hidden states and
estimate parameters from a single or multiple sequences of a discrete time
Hidden Markov Model. The observed values can be modeled by a multinomial
distribution for categorical/labeled emissions, a mixture of Gaussians for
continuous data and also a mixture of Poissons for discrete values. It
includes functions for random initialization, simulation, backward or
forward sequence evaluation, Viterbi or forward-backward decoding and
parameter estimation using an Expectation-Maximization approach.

